## Overview

This lab explores two of the most widely deployed access control models in enterprise IAM:

|Model   |Full Name                     |Core Idea                                                                       |
|--------|------------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|**RBAC**|Role-Based Access Control     |Access is granted based on a user’s **role** in the organization                |
|**ABAC**|Attribute-Based Access Control|Access is granted based on **attributes** of the user, resource, and environment|

### How Access Decisions Are Made

```
RBAC Decision Flow:
  User → assigned Role → Role has Permissions → Access Granted/Denied

ABAC Decision Flow:
  User Attributes + Resource Attributes + Environment Attributes → Policy Engine → Access Granted/Denied
```

