## Part 2 — ABAC Lab

### Core ABAC Model

Unlike RBAC, ABAC evaluates **attributes** at decision time. Access decisions consider:

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                      ABAC MODEL                             │
│                                                             │
│  Subject Attributes    Resource Attributes   Environment    │
│  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────┐  │
│  │ username: alice │  │ type: EHR        │  │ time:    │  │
│  │ role: Nurse     │  │ sensitivity: HIGH│  │ 08:00    │  │
│  │ dept: Oncology  │  │ dept: Oncology   │  │ IP:      │  │
│  │ clearance: L2   │  │ owner: bob.smith │  │ 10.0.1.5 │  │
│  └────────┬────────┘  └────────┬─────────┘  └────┬─────┘  │
│           │                    │                  │         │
│           └──────────┬─────────┘                  │         │
│                      │         ┌───────────────────┘         │
│                      ▼         ▼                             │
│               ┌─────────────────────┐                       │
│               │   Policy Engine     │                       │
│               │  (PDP - Policy      │                       │
│               │   Decision Point)   │                       │
│               └──────────┬──────────┘                       │
│                          │                                  │
│               ┌──────────▼──────────┐                       │
│               │  PERMIT / DENY      │                       │
│               └─────────────────────┘                       │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### ABAC Architecture Components

|Component                  |Acronym|Role                                            |
|---------------------------|-------|------------------------------------------------|
|Policy Enforcement Point   |**PEP**|Intercepts the request and enforces the decision|
|Policy Decision Point      |**PDP**|Evaluates the policy and returns Permit/Deny    |
|Policy Information Point   |**PIP**|Retrieves attribute values                      |
|Policy Administration Point|**PAP**|Where policies are authored and stored          |

-----

### 2.1 ABAC Concepts and Policy Design

A policy in ABAC is a logical expression:

```
POLICY: "Allow access to patient records IF..."
  subject.role        == "Nurse"           AND
  subject.department  == resource.department  AND
  resource.type       == "PatientRecord"   AND
  environment.time    >= 06:00             AND
  environment.time    <= 22:00
```

This is far more **granular** than RBAC — the same user (Nurse) might be denied access to a patient in a **different department**, even with the same role.

