## Part 3 — RBAC vs ABAC Comparison

### Decision Flowchart

```
                        ACCESS REQUEST
                             │
                             ▼
              ┌──────────────────────────┐
              │  What model are we using?│
              └──────────┬───────────────┘
                         │
           ┌─────────────┴─────────────┐
           ▼                           ▼
        RBAC                         ABAC
           │                           │
           ▼                           ▼
   "What role does             "What are the attributes
    this user have?"            of user, resource, env?"
           │                           │
           ▼                           ▼
   Lookup role →               Evaluate policy rules
   check permissions            against all attributes
           │                           │
           ▼                           ▼
     GRANT / DENY               PERMIT / DENY
```

### Feature Comparison

|Feature                      |RBAC                           |ABAC                                     |
|-----------------------------|-------------------------------|-----------------------------------------|
|**Access basis**             |User’s role                    |Attributes of user, resource, environment|
|**Granularity**              |Coarse (role-level)            |Fine-grained (per attribute combination) |
|**Policy language**          |Role → Permission mappings     |Boolean expressions over attributes      |
|**Scalability**              |Role explosion risk at scale   |Scales cleanly via attributes            |
|**Implementation complexity**|Low                            |Medium to High                           |
|**Admin overhead**           |Low initially, grows with roles|Higher upfront, lower at scale           |
|**Dynamic context**          |❌ Not native                   |✅ Yes (time, location, device)           |
|**Regulatory alignment**     |HIPAA (basic), SOX             |HIPAA, HITRUST, Zero Trust               |
|**Common in**                |AD, Azure, most IAM tools      |AWS IAM, SailPoint, Saviynt, OPA         |
|**Best for**                 |Small/mid orgs, stable roles   |Large orgs, dynamic access needs         |

### When to Use Which

```
Use RBAC when:
  ✅ Your org has well-defined, stable job roles
  ✅ Access needs are consistent per role
  ✅ Team is less mature with IAM tooling
  ✅ You need fast, simple implementation
  ✅ Using AD groups as your primary control

Use ABAC when:
  ✅ You need fine-grained, contextual access
  ✅ Same role should see different data by department
  ✅ Time-based or location-based policies are required
  ✅ You're implementing Zero Trust architecture
  ✅ Contractor/vendor access must be tightly scoped
  ✅ You have SailPoint, Saviynt, or OPA in your stack
```

